race.comment: CATCH SOME RAYS (5) was out of the placings last time when fifth at Capalaba (20.06) but scored three back at this track (19.01). Has a good record here at this journey. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to his credit. Can atone. CHAVERO (7) has been impressive at his past couple of wins, the best coming last time at Warragul in 25.93. Winner at his latest appearance in the quickest time on the card. Expecting another bold showing. AFTER THE SIREN (1) was impressive last start despite finishing second, recording a dominant 19.19 to place behind Make Me King and clocking a new PB this course and distance. Should be in this for a long way. WINKING WILLIE (3) hit the frame here last start and can sneak into the finish again.
